<br>
It is her right to post here, and she does bring a breather ( the board can get pretty whiny once in a while ). I am almost in favor of giving her her own part of the board though, because I feel ( maybe it's because my character 'grew up' on his own ) that she is being handed the game on a silver platter, and that there are actually other sections of the boards she should be posting on.<br>
<br>
And it is unfortunately true that many newbies asked questions over the boards, and few ever got the kind of response Dracca did get ( even though they asked just as nicely ). Why? I'm not going to get into that. What I mean is -<br>
maybe she should play the game a bit, instead of asking here for just about everything.<br>
<br>
I am not saying that she necessarily is manipulating everyone for her evil conspiracy of becoming the tower's Mascotte ( not to mention the most twinked main mage to ever exist ). However, I do believe everyone is entitled to suspicions, and freedom of speech over the boards should be a given, I think, when flames are not forthcoming with it.<br>
<br>
I know very well I'm the minority here. I was also civil about my opinion, so I hope this does not elicit any flames ( and certainly not the need to lock the thread ). <p>Forever sharp is the sword of Justice.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dukeofthesky>Duke of the sky</A> at: 2/15/03 6:29:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gamrok>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 449<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 5:29:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I strongly disagree</span><hr size=1> Dalren was the first to flame.  It would have been best to leave the thread locked so that we could quote from it, (although I'm sure it's probably in a moderator only section of some sorts) to prove anything we have to say.  Tydemage asked a legitimate question.  He didn't use the best tone, grammar or choice of words, but there wasn't any &quot;flame&quot; in his first post.  However, in the third or fourth post of the thread, Dalren sends out the first flame.<br>
